{"article_id":"Svd9MJdz46RzP6QJ","edus":[{"id":0,"text":"The number of new coronavirus tests","depth":7},{"id":1,"text":"reported each day","depth":7},{"id":2,"text":"has plateaued","depth":6},{"id":3,"text":"- a big blow to the prospects","depth":7},{"id":4,"text":"of America reopening its economy safely anytime soon ,","depth":7},{"id":5,"text":"even as President Donald Trump insists","depth":7},{"id":6,"text":"the country is weeks away from doing so .","depth":7},{"id":7,"text":"Trump announced guidelines on April 16","depth":8},{"id":8,"text":"for states to reopen ,","depth":8},{"id":9,"text":"calling for governors to ease social distancing measures , such as stay-at-home orders ,","depth":8},{"id":10,"text":"as the number of new coronavirus cases begin to come down .","depth":8},{"id":11,"text":"He acknowledged","depth":7},{"id":12,"text":"a requirement","depth":11},{"id":13,"text":"for reopening the economy","depth":11},{"id":14,"text":"is that the federal government and states must know","depth":10},{"id":15,"text":"that the numbers of new coronavirus cases are actually coming down ;","depth":9},{"id":16,"text":"without widespread testing ,","depth":9},{"id":17,"text":"they simply can ' t know","depth":10},{"id":18,"text":"what they ' re dealing with and how to act .","depth":10},{"id":19,"text":"\" Our best scientists & health experts assess","depth":12},{"id":20,"text":"that states today have enough tests","depth":13},{"id":21,"text":"to implement the criteria of phase one ,","depth":14},{"id":22,"text":"if they choose , \"","depth":14},{"id":23,"text":"Vice President Mike Pence said at a press conference the night of April 17 .","depth":11},{"id":24,"text":"But","depth":11},{"id":25,"text":"according to the Covid Tracking Project ,","depth":12},{"id":26,"text":"the US has averaged fewer than 150,000 tests each day so far in the week of April 13 , including at both public and commercial labs .","depth":12},{"id":27,"text":"That ' s an improvement from the early days of March ,","depth":11},{"id":28,"text":"when the country reported new tests in the dozens and later the hundreds .","depth":11},{"id":29,"text":"But it ' s not an increase from more recent weeks :","depth":11},{"id":30,"text":"In the week of April 6 , the country also averaged fewer than 150,000 tests a day .","depth":11},{"id":31,"text":"What the country needs","depth":12},{"id":32,"text":"to properly do testing ,","depth":12},{"id":33,"text":"according to experts ,","depth":11},{"id":34,"text":"is at least 500,000 tests a day .","depth":10},{"id":35,"text":"Some experts call for much more than that","depth":11},{"id":36,"text":"- millions or even tens of millions a day -","depth":11},{"id":37,"text":"but the general point is that the US needs to be doing multiple times the testing","depth":12},{"id":38,"text":"that it ' s currently doing","depth":12},{"id":39,"text":"to be able to test everyone with symptoms and their close contacts .","depth":11},{"id":40,"text":"A recognition of that fact is perhaps the biggest reason","depth":9},{"id":41,"text":"the US is social distancing now .","depth":9},{"id":42,"text":"One of the big goals during this period is to flatten the curve","depth":10},{"id":43,"text":"- reducing the spread of the virus -","depth":10},{"id":44,"text":"as the US scales up testing and surveillance systems","depth":10},{"id":45,"text":"to let the nation and states better control new clusters of cases .","depth":10},{"id":46,"text":"\" The whole point of this social distancing is to buy us time","depth":9},{"id":47,"text":"to build up capacity","depth":10},{"id":48,"text":"to do the types of public health interventions","depth":11},{"id":49,"text":"we know","depth":12},{"id":50,"text":"work , \"","depth":12},{"id":51,"text":"Natalie Dean , a biostatistics professor at the University of Florida , told me .","depth":8},{"id":52,"text":"\" If we ' re not using this time","depth":10},{"id":53,"text":"to scale up testing to the level","depth":11},{"id":54,"text":"that we need it to be ...","depth":11},{"id":55,"text":"we don ' t have an exit strategy .","depth":9},{"id":56,"text":"And then","depth":9},{"id":57,"text":"when we lift things ,","depth":10},{"id":58,"text":"we ' re no better equipped","depth":11},{"id":59,"text":"than we were before . \"","depth":11},{"id":60,"text":"Testing gives officials the means","depth":7},{"id":61,"text":"to isolate sick people ,","depth":8},{"id":62,"text":"track and quarantine the people","depth":10},{"id":63,"text":"whom","depth":13},{"id":64,"text":"those verified to be sick","depth":13},{"id":65,"text":"came into close contact with","depth":12},{"id":66,"text":"( a.k.a . \" contact tracing \" ) ,","depth":11},{"id":67,"text":"and deploy community-wide efforts","depth":10},{"id":68,"text":"if a new cluster of cases is too large and uncontrolled otherwise .","depth":10},{"id":69,"text":"Without it , the only way","depth":9},{"id":70,"text":"to deal with the outbreak","depth":9},{"id":71,"text":"is more social distancing ,","depth":8},{"id":72,"text":"which further hurts the economy ,","depth":8},{"id":73,"text":"or letting the disease run its course","depth":9},{"id":74,"text":"- at the cost of potentially hundreds of thousands or millions of lives .","depth":9},{"id":75,"text":"The recent slowdown in new tests is driven by shortages in nasal swabs , personal protective equipment , reagents , test kits , and machines","depth":7},{"id":76,"text":"needed to run the specific tests","depth":8},{"id":77,"text":"required .","depth":8},{"id":78,"text":"According to David Lim at Politico ,","depth":8},{"id":79,"text":"some labs also complain","depth":8},{"id":80,"text":"that the Centers for Disease Control and Prevention ' s testing criteria","depth":10},{"id":81,"text":"- which prioritizes hospitalized patients , health care workers , and those vulnerable to the virus , such as older people -","depth":10},{"id":82,"text":"is holding back potential tests ,","depth":9},{"id":83,"text":"leaving existing testing capacity unused .","depth":8},{"id":84,"text":"To fix the gaps ,","depth":10},{"id":85,"text":"experts argue ,","depth":10},{"id":86,"text":"the federal government needs to relax criteria for testing ,","depth":10},{"id":87,"text":"invest in new supplies and labs ,","depth":11},{"id":88,"text":"and better coordinate supply chains","depth":12},{"id":89,"text":"to address , among other issues , chokepoints .","depth":12},{"id":90,"text":"States , with limited resources and little control of the national supply chain , simply can ' t do this all on their own .","depth":8},{"id":91,"text":"Such fixes , however , are easier said than done .","depth":8},{"id":92,"text":"Experts warn","depth":10},{"id":93,"text":"the next phase of testing will be much more difficult than the initial phase ,","depth":11},{"id":94,"text":"which largely required getting existing labs to start doing coronavirus testing","depth":12},{"id":95,"text":"- the low-hanging fruit .","depth":12},{"id":96,"text":"\" We ' ve made substantial progress","depth":12},{"id":97,"text":"ramping testing this month , \"","depth":12},{"id":98,"text":"Scott Gottlieb , a former commissioner of the Food and Drug Administration , wrote in a tweet on April 10 .","depth":11},{"id":99,"text":"\" But many gains were made","depth":12},{"id":100,"text":"by getting players into fight","depth":13},{"id":101,"text":"( clinical labs , academic labs ) .","depth":13},{"id":102,"text":"Now we must expand lab capacity , platforms , throughput , test kits .","depth":12},{"id":103,"text":"Getting next million tests/week will be harder","depth":13},{"id":104,"text":"than getting first . \"","depth":13},{"id":105,"text":"This is one reason","depth":7},{"id":106,"text":"the plans","depth":9},{"id":107,"text":"to end social distancing","depth":9},{"id":108,"text":"are so grim :","depth":8},{"id":109,"text":"Not only do they suggest","depth":8},{"id":110,"text":"that some level of social distancing will be needed for the next year or so","depth":10},{"id":111,"text":"( until a vaccine or a similarly effective treatment is widely available )","depth":10},{"id":112,"text":"- which we don ' t know","depth":10},{"id":113,"text":"if the country can sustain -","depth":10},{"id":114,"text":"but they call for a level of surveillance and testing","depth":8},{"id":115,"text":"the US simply hasn ' t yet shown the ability and willingness","depth":9},{"id":116,"text":"to build and manage .","depth":9},{"id":117,"text":"It ' s possible the US could get a lucky break ;","depth":7},{"id":118,"text":"there ' s still a lot about the coronavirus","depth":10},{"id":119,"text":"that we don ' t know ,","depth":10},{"id":120,"text":"and maybe","depth":10},{"id":121,"text":"as we learn more ,","depth":12},{"id":122,"text":"we ' ll realize","depth":12},{"id":123,"text":"the country can be spared the worst .","depth":11},{"id":124,"text":"( That ' s optimistic ,","depth":10},{"id":125,"text":"given the outbreaks","depth":11},{"id":126,"text":"we ' ve already seen across the globe ,","depth":11},{"id":127,"text":"but it ' s possible . )","depth":9},{"id":128,"text":"The Trump administration and states also still have time","depth":4},{"id":129,"text":"to ease testing criteria","depth":5},{"id":130,"text":"and scale up capacity in the coming weeks .","depth":5},{"id":131,"text":"But","depth":5},{"id":132,"text":"unless something changes ,","depth":6},{"id":133,"text":"America is simply not meeting the benchmark of aggressive testing","depth":7},{"id":134,"text":"that experts say","depth":9},{"id":135,"text":"is necessary","depth":9},{"id":136,"text":"to start to reopen the country .","depth":8},{"id":137,"text":"As eager as Trump is to get the economy going again ,","depth":5},{"id":138,"text":"the US just isn ' t ready to do it in a safe way yet .","depth":5},{"id":139,"text":"Every day at , we aim to answer your most important questions","depth":4},{"id":140,"text":"and provide you , and our audience around the world , with information","depth":5},{"id":141,"text":"that has the power","depth":6},{"id":142,"text":"to save lives .","depth":6},{"id":143,"text":"Our mission has never been more vital","depth":6},{"id":144,"text":"than it is in this moment :","depth":6},{"id":145,"text":"to empower you","depth":6},{"id":146,"text":"through understanding .","depth":6},{"id":147,"text":"' s work is reaching more people than ever ,","depth":5},{"id":148,"text":"but our distinctive brand of explanatory journalism takes resources","depth":6},{"id":149,"text":"- particularly during a pandemic and an economic downturn .","depth":6},{"id":150,"text":"Your financial contribution will not constitute a donation ,","depth":4},{"id":151,"text":"but it will enable our staff to continue to offer free articles , videos , and podcasts at the quality and volume","depth":5},{"id":152,"text":"that this moment requires .","depth":5},{"id":153,"text":"Please consider making a contribution to today .","depth":3}],"relations":[{"parent":307,"left":292,"right":306,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":292,"left":281,"right":291,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":281,"left":213,"right":280,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":213,"left":160,"right":212,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":160,"left":156,"right":159,"relation":"causal","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":156,"left":155,"right":2,"relation":"same-unit","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":155,"left":0,"right":1,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":159,"left":157,"right":158,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":157,"left":3,"right":4,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":158,"left":5,"right":6,"relation":"attribution","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":212,"left":171,"right":211,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":171,"left":163,"right":170,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":163,"left":161,"r